				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I really enjoyed the tone &#8211; the whole cowboy wild west thing is beyond overdone and way into cool again. Really liked the mosey and chewed up nails and gander etc for this piece.</p>
<p>The fantasy element works well and I like the everydayness of the silver bullets kept in the safe. Paragraph structure really bugged me &#8211; don&#8217;t know if WP just messed up your formatting or it was intentional.</p>
<p>My only crit is on the reveal of the werewolf thing &#8211; seems kind of clumsy with some strange confusions in lines like: &#8216;Full moon. Makes everybody act the fool.&#8217; and &#8216;start to smell things a little stronger than afore&#8217;</p>
<p>These distracted me from understanding in that it confused exactly who the wolf is for me.</p>
<p>The end and the undertakers place is great &#8211; like the beginning the super overdone ideas fresh and new in the werewolf context.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

